Rating: 4
I made this again yesterday for a dinner party. Excellent! Of course I had to tweak it a bit. I used only 1/2 c. sugar plus the preserves. This amount of sugar is perfect, especially if you serve the pie with ice cream. I also cooked the sugar, spice, and apple mixture in the microwave to prevent the gap between crust and fruit. I microwaved the mixture on high in 3 minute intervals, just until the apples were starting to turn translucent and the juices were glossy. This took about 11 minutes in my microwave. I used a different pie crust recipe, a basic crust with butter and shortening. I covered the crust with foil, but missed one edge that got too brown. Oh well, it was still a delicious pie.

