Rating: 4
I made this pie last year for Thanksgiving, and I plan to make it again this year. I did a dry run last weekend. I changed just one thing in this recipe: I sauted the apples, sugar, spices, preserves, and cherries in butter before filling the pie crust. This method solves the problem of the gap between the crust and the apple filling. However, while cooking the apples long enough to slightly soften, the sugar started to caramelize. I liked the flavor, but I didn't like how dark the filling ended up. For the real deal this week, I will cook the apples for few minutes, and then add the sugar and preserves and cook for a few. Total cooking time <10 minutes. Then I plan to spread them on a sheet pan to cool, and that's when I will sprinkle them with the spices and add the cherries. I also plan to cut the sugar to 2/3 cup. I'll let you know how this version turns out!

